"My cabby drove fast. I don't think I ever drove faster, but the others were there before us. The
cab and the landau with their steaming horses were in front of the door when I arrived. I paid the
man and hurried into the church. There was not a soul there save the two whom I had followed and a
surpliced clergyman, who seemed to be expostulating with them. They were all three standing in a
knot in front of the altar. I lounged up the side aisle like any other idler who has dropped into a
church. Suddenly, to my surprise, the three at the altar faced round to me, and Godfrey Norton came
running as hard as he could towards me.

"'Thank God,' he cried. 'You'll do. Come! Come!'

"'What then?' I asked.

"'Come, man, come, only three minutes, or it won't be legal.'